FBIS4-23860 "drafr117_d_94009" FBIS-AFR-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Zambia Road Transport Agreement Signed With Namibia Road Transport Agreement Signed With Namibia MB1606183894 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network in English 1800 GMT 16 Jun 94 MB1606183894 Lusaka Zambia National Broadcasting Corporation Network English BFN [Text] Zambia and Namibia have signed a road transport agreement and are working out plans to build a bridge across the Zambezi River to easy transborder crossing. Speaking during a signing ceremony to mark the end of the first session of the Zambia-Namibia Joint Permanent Commission of Communication, Deputy Minister of Transport and Communications Gilbert Mululu said the commission noted the importance of Zambia utilizing the Walvis Bay in the transportation of cargo. In energy, the minister said Zambia expressed willingness to consider Namibia's interest to import more electricity above the current supply and the introduction of border passes to facilitate border crossings for people living around the border boundaries.
